adram is a settlement in the municipality of Oplotnica in eastern Slovenia. It lies immediately to the east of Oplotnica itself. The area is part of the traditional region of Lower Styria. The municipality is now included in the Drava statistical region.
A church on Lana gora hill to the northwest of the settlement is dedicated to Saints Hermagoras and Fortunatus and belongs to the parish of adram-Oplotnica. It dates to the 14th century with 17th-century restyling.

